description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you have a passion for acute patient-centred care? Are you looking for a new challenge within a friendly supportive team? We are looking for registered nurses to join us on Ward 20.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a 30 bedded acute medical ward with 100% single rooms. We work in three teams on the ward and have a senior Nurse in Charge on every shift. We have developed a good team spirit and friendly atmosphere. Ward 20 is a busy area that currently specialises in Diabetes and endocrinology there are 2 resident consultants and their junior doctors that work closely with the nursing team, our patients have a wide age range and conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Maidstone and Tunbridge Wells NHS Trust we believe that our staff are our biggest asset. With staff welfare top of the agenda, we nurture excellence, professionalism and are committed to staff development with the support of our practice development team. We have a comprehensive education package to ensure our staff provide the best care for our patients. We are committed to equality of opportunity and providing a healthy working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to attend the Trust’s Induction Programme for RNs, RMs and ODPs (which starts on the first day of employment). The programme is full-time (please contact the programme lead if this is problematic: nicola.henthorn@nhs.net), lasts for two weeks and will involve travelling to both Trust sites. The programme includes supernumerary shifts in the clinical area and classroom-based study days which run from 9am to 5pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that appointment to this post will be subject to a satisfactory Disclosure &amp; Barring Service Check at &lt;strong&gt;enhanced level. (Enhanced level now includes regulated checks against vulnerable adults and children)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are passionate in supporting our staff to develop and have great opportunities for career progression. We take equality and diversity seriously and seek to empower all diverse groups within our trust. We seek to develop a culture where diversity in all its forms is celebrated. We are committed to ensuring that women are empowered to work at all levels of management and that working patterns are as flexible as possible giving all members of staff opportunity to flourish in using their skills for our patients. We work across our trust to enable those who consider themselves to have a disability both visible and invisible to have access to all they need to thrive in their work environment. We work with Stonewall to embed an inclusive and accepting culture for all lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender staff. We have 78 nationalities working in our trust and we are proud of this. We are active in embracing the ethnic and cultural diversity in our trust. We work to empower people with any protected characteristic to have opportunities to work in an environment that helps them to contribute to the best of their ability, recognising and valuing the unique contributions each of us brings for best quality care and service to our patients. We are committed to supporting the delivery of the Equality Act with zero tolerance for any discrimination, harassment or victimisation of applicants and staff with these protected characteristics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: Friday 13th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews: Friday 20th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sakheleni Makena, Ward Manager, makena@nhs.net, 01892 635613/ 635191&lt;/p&gt;
